[2] Japan: Sharp rise in cases
Date: Fri 17 Jul 2020
Source: NHK [edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200717/k10012520301000.html


The Tokyo Metropolitan Government announced on 17 Jul 2020 that it had confirmed that 293 people in Tokyo [under the age of 10 to 90. sic] were newly infected with the new coronavirus. The number confirmed per day in Tokyo exceeded the number of 286 people on the previous day, 16 Jul 2020, [which was ]the highest number [to date].

According to the capital, out of 293 people, the total number of people in their 20s and 30s was 210, accounting for more than 70% of the total, while the total number of people in their 40s and 50s was 58, close to 20% of the total.

151 out of [the] 293 people were close contacts of people confirmed to have been infected [already], and the infection route of the remaining 142 people is not yet known. 69 of the 293 are employees and customers at host clubs, cabaret clubs, and other stores that entertain. Of these, 49 were in the Shinjuku area.

In addition, there are 24 diners, 10 at facilities such as nursing homes and medical institutions, 16 at home, 15 at work, and guests at stage performances in theaters in Shinjuku Ward. Also, 10 students were infected at a training camp in the sports club of Chuo University.

This makes a total of 8933 people confirmed infected in Tokyo. But no deaths were confirmed on 17 Jul 2020 in Tokyo.

Tokyo is aiming to increase the number of beds for patients from 1000 to 2800 in response to the increase in the number of people infected with the new coronavirus. As of 16 Jul 2020, the number of beds actually secured was over 1500. Experts are concerned that the speed of increasing patients may exceed the number of beds.

--
