[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 660 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Sun 19 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-07/19/c_81112.htm


On 18 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 19 Jul 2020):
- 16 new cases of confirmed infections (3 imported cases, 2 in Guangdong province and 1 in Shandong province; 13 indigenous cases in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region), 1 new case of suspected infections (an imported case in Shanghai municipality), and no deaths.
- A total of 2007 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 660 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 775 recovered and discharged from hospital; 771 589 close contacts with infected patients; and 6925 are under medical observation.
- 42 new asymptomatic cases (including 12 imported); no asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 147 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 87 imported cases).
- 1777 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 64 cases since 17 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau and 454 in Taiwan.

