[There were 16 new confirmed cases in the past 24 hours; 3 were imported, and 13 were locally acquired in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region. While it is now 13 days with no new cases reported from Beijing, it appears another cluster is under way in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region. According to another media report, the area will do mass testing.

There were 42 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals (12 imported) and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, China has reported 37 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infection.

Hong Kong reported 64 new cases. The CHP HK page, however, mentions a total case number of 1778 cases in Hong Kong so far (comprising 1777 confirmed cases and one probable case). The newly reported cases announced today [19 Jul 2020] involve 23 males and 41 females aged between 16 and 86 years. Among them, 4 had travel history during the incubation period. (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/16/P2020071600800.htm).

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2. Hong Kong is dealing with increased local transmission associated with the lifting of restrictions; new severe restrictions have been announced.

