[D] Iran: 271 606 total cases, 13 979 deaths
Date: Sat 18 Jul 2020 14:05 GMT
Source: IRNA, AP, and Reuters [edited]
https://www.rferl.org/a/rohani-coronavirus-25-million-iranians-infected/30734897.html

Iranian president, Hassan Rohani, on 18 Jul 2020 estimated that as many as 25 million Iranians could have been infected with the coronavirus since the beginning of the outbreak, as he urged the public to take the pandemic seriously. Rohani cited a new study by the Health Ministry in offering the unprecedentedly high number of 25 million coronavirus cases. Iran's population is around 81 million people. "Our estimate is that until now 25 million Iranians have been infected with this virus and about 14 000 have lost their dear lives," Rohani said.

"The report says that there is the possibility that between 30 and 35 million other people will be at risk," he said. Rohani said more than 200 000 people had been hospitalized, while adding that the number was expected to double in the coming months. He did not say what the report's estimates were based on. The study has so far not been made public.

Experts and others have long said that real numbers of coronavirus cases in Iran are higher than the confirmed figures. A parliamentary report released in April 2020 said Iran's death toll is likely nearly double the officially reported figures. Given insufficient testing, the report said the number of people infected at the time was probably "8 to 10 times" higher than the confirmed figures.

According to the latest figures released by the Health Ministry on 18 Jul 2020, Iran has 271 606 infections while the death toll stands at 13 979. In recent weeks, Iran has seen a surge in its daily death toll.

Authorities on 18 Jul 2020 reimposed one-week restrictions in the capital, Tehran, including banning religious and cultural functions, closing cafes, indoor pools, amusement parks, and zoos in an effort to contain the deadly pandemic.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 18 Jul 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran is 271 606, including 13 979 deaths, an increase of 2166 cases and 188 deaths since 17 Jul 2020. According to another media report, there are now 8 provinces with the highest incidences of COVID-19 in the country (Khuzestan, Razavi Khorasan, East and West Azerbaijan, Mazandaran, Golestan, Bushehr, and Hormozgan) and an additional 6 provinces at high risk (Tehran, Fars, Kerman, Alborz, Kohgiluyeh, and Boyer-Ahmad; https://www.aa.com.tr/en/asia-pacific/iran-reports-over-180-more-virus-fatalities/1913846).

